social_posts.post_text: This morning my sister & I went to our local Veterans cemetery to lay wreaths for the Wreaths Across America ceremony. We laid wreaths on graves, said their names, thanked them for their service & said a prayer. We made this a tradition to go every year after our papo passed in honor of him. This year was extra special because we got to bring Tex with us & I know papo was smiling down watching. He was a Veteran himself & volunteered many of hours helping other Veterans. We will continue to honor his legacy. “Remember and Honor our Veterans, teach the next generation to do the same.” 🇺🇸 miss you everyday papo 🤍
